# RentaFlow — Claude Rules

## Stack (do not ask, do not explain basics)
- React 18 + Vite 5 SPA (no react-router, useState-based routing)
- localStorage primary data layer via storage.js / lib/db.js
- Supabase Auth optional (VITE_USE_AUTH flag)
- Express 4 backend on Railway
- i18next for i18n (fr default, ar, en)
- jsPDF + jspdf-autotable for PDFs
- lucide-react for icons
- All DB calls go through lib/db.js — assume it exists, do not rewrite it

## Response rules
- Do NOT explain basic React/JS/CSS syntax
- Do NOT generate boilerplate comments or summaries after a change
- When fixing a bug: output only the changed lines with enough context to locate them — NOT the whole file
- When adding a feature: output only the new/changed code blocks
- Do NOT restate what the user asked — go straight to the code
- Prefer Edit tool over Write tool for existing files
- Keep responses short and direct

## Code rules
- No Tailwind — use CSS variables and existing class names (btn, card, form-input, etc.)
- No new npm packages without asking first
- camelCase in frontend, snake_case in Supabase/SQL
- All monetary values in MAD
- Dates stored as ISO strings (YYYY-MM-DD)
